<TEXT>
when the weather heats up sperm production goes 
down and this may explain why fewer babies are born in the 
springtime according to a study today 
while the study documents that men produce less sperm during the 
summer it does not definitely explain why 
population experts have long noticed that fewer babies are born 
in the spring months than at any other time of the year 
the researchers based at the chemical industry institute of 
toxicology in research triangle park nc dismissed one obvious 
explanation for the summertime dearth of conceptions 
they said that the available evidence does not support the 
idea that because its so hot people simply have sex less often in 
the summer 
what they found instead was that semen quality deteriorates 
during the summer 
this phenomenon may account at least in part for the reduction 
in the birth rate during the spring in regions with warm 
climates the researchers concluded 
the study directed by dr richard h levine was published in 
the new england journal of medicine it was conducted on 131 men in 
steamy san antonio texas 
all of the men worked outdoors at least part of the day their 
sperm concentrations were onethird lower in summer than in winter 
about 18 percent of their children were born in the spring 
compared with almost 30 percent in the fall 
there can no longer be any doubt that concentrationrelated 
measures of semen quality are reduced during the summer the 
researchers wrote 
exactly why however is unclear high temperatures interfere 
with the testicles ability to make sperm but in this study 
summer sperm production was lower even in those who spent part of 
the day inside in air conditioning so torrid summer weather may 
not be the whole answer 
the immediate implications of these findings is that although 
sperm counts are lower in the summer the mediating factor is not 
the heat of the summer wrote dr peter j snyder of the 
university of pennsylvania 
in an editorial in the journal he suggested another possible 
explanation maybe its the extra daylight not the heat that 
makes men less fertile in the summertime 
</TEXT>
