<TEXT>
the 30 youths from around the country 
assembled at this summer sleepaway camp are here to study torts 
not sports 
welcome to the national lawcamp the child of a recently 
graduated lawyers shock bewilderment and fear during his first 
weeks of law school 
the camp offers students an introduction to law study without 
the intense grade competition the imposing professors personified 
by the late john houseman in the movie paper chase and without 
the hefty cost 
one of the things i saw was that a lot of students use their 
first year of law school to see if thats what they want to do 
said camp organizer chris salamone a fort lauderdale litigator who 
got his law degree two years ago from nearby nova university 
the threeweek camp is aimed at letting students know what 
theyre in for at law school for 1995 compared to typical 
tuitions that run into five figures the campers range from age 15 
to the mid20s and if theyre certain thats what they want the 
camp should give them a headstart on the oftenmystifying law 
school experience said salamone 
his father anthony has 30 years experience running summer 
sports camps mostly in new jersey and is helping get lawcamp 
going 
the students staying on the barry university campus in this 
miami suburb will find out about the heavy workload and the 
competition in a law career salamone said legal ethics also will 
be stressed 
were not all michael cusacks nova law professor michael 
flynn referring to an la law television lawyer told 
students as the camp opened sunday evening we spend very long 
hours its very hard work thats all 
ellis rubin one of miamis bestknown defense attorneys was 
the camps first guest lecturer 
you have to pay your dues you have to put in extra hours 
its very difficult to break in rubin said if you reach a 
point where youre valuable to other people then you will receive 
your reward 
rubin an attorney 39 years said that only in the past 15 years 
has he earned a comfortable living 
if after hearing such deglamorizing accounts students decide 
against a law career salamone said they have saved law school 
tuition and spent three weeks in south florida and you will know 
more law than 99 percent of americans so that cant hurt 
the campers will be taught by law professors who then stay 
around to study with them and answer questions salamone said that 
law professors often are inaccessible leaving beginning students 
confused and scared 
law school concentrates on analysis and procedure rather than 
the simple answeroriented teaching most students are used to 
salamone said 
law schools dont tell you what theyre doing they just do 
it salamone said 
the camp also offers mock trials and a law school admission test 
seminar and sample test 
its perfect for this time in my life said jennifer 
edwards a florida international university junior who hasnt 
decided on a career im not really sure what im going to do 
im hoping this will kind of push me over the edge 
sixteenyearold voselyn williams a senior at miami archbishop 
curleynotre dame high school plans to become a corporate lawyer 
she sees the camp as good preparation 
i dont want to go into anything blind she said 
as with any summer camp there are field trips to the broward 
county courthouse jail and crime lab 
its not all statute books and case studies time is planned for 
pool lounging softball volleyball and something that could come 
in handy after the future lawyers send their clients bills out a 
martial arts demonstration 
