<TEXT>
marion rice hart an adventurer who 
sailed around the world and made seven solo flights across the 
atlantic died monday of pneumonia at age 98 
she didnt start flying until age 54 but went on to earn 
worldwide acclaim for her feats 
hart was born oct 2 1891 in london she married mining 
engineer arthur hart and the couple lived in arizona and 
california before divorcing 
hart piloted her singleengine plane nonstop across the 
atlantic at age 61 she later flew all over the united states 
europe asia africa and south america and made at least six more 
solo flights across the atlantic the last at age 83 
in 1936 hart cast off for what became a threeyear voyage 
sailing around the world on her 72foot ketch 
books she wrote about her exploits include i fly as i 
please how to navigate today and who called that lady a 
skipper 
she died at alta bates hospital in berkeley 
</TEXT>
