industry 
while short on specifics the ministrys vision for the 1990s 
addresses many of the demands for economic reform made by the 
united states in talks that led to last months agreement on ways 
to tackle the us trade deficit with japan 
these include a push for more spending at home on public works 
such as roads sewers and parks areas in which japan lags 
behind other major developed nations a summary of the report 
said 
