pay 
it was an oblique admission that prices have been kept 
artificially high by governmentprotected home markets where the 
staple food rice costs several times more than on world markets 
the ministrys criticism seems to contradict its own annual 
white paper issued two weeks ago which concluded that the high 
trade surplus with the united states was caused by natural factors 
not closed markets 
the report also warns however that manufacturing is still 
vital to japans economy it recommends that the government nearly 
