donated to the louvre in 1961 by french collector victor lion 
rosenberg said renoir was a magic name among art lovers 
which could explain the theft the first at the louvre in more 
than 10 years 
sallois said there was no evidence of negligence on the part of 
museum guards and expressed confidence in the staff 
