the berlin wall effectively fell on nov 9 when communists who 
had ousted hardline leader erich honecker lifted all travel 
restrictions for east germans in an effort to retain power 
since then the graffiticovered wall the most visible symbol 
of the cold war has been torn down in dozens of places 
all controls on the eastwest border ended when the two germanys 
merged their economies on july 1 berlins most famous border 
crossing checkpoint charlie was hoisted into history late last 
month 
the wall was built on aug 13 1961 to stem the flow of east 
germans trying to escape to the west during repressive communist 
