<TEXT>
fans enraged by englands loss to west germany in 
world cup soccer rioted in 30 english towns in a night of violence 
that left three dead dozens injured and 600 under arrest police 
said thursday 
the rioting mostly in southern england broke out wednesday 
night after fans watching live broadcasts from the semifinal in 
italy poured into the streets when west germany defeated england 
43 
more than 35 police officers were injured in clashes with the 
rioters 
in the southern resort town of brighton 500 fans roamed the 
