<TEXT>
the mitch snyder who forced a president to 
provide shelter for washingtons street people was a singleminded 
oftenabrasive advocate for the homeless 
the mitch snyder who apparently ended his life thursday in his 
room at a homeless shelter was a man who struggled with religious 
beliefs and was tormented by his abandonment of his young sons two 
decades ago 
snyder once described himself as dedicated to liberating 
people who are destitute but his confrontational style drew 
criticism sometimes from other homeless activists 
when snyder was on a hunger strike to force the white house to 
pay for shelter improvements rep e clay shaw rfla called 
him a masochist who influences government by threatening to 
starve himself 
raised in new york city snyder married young and had two sons 
but after a series of unsuccessful jobs he walked out on his 
family in 1969 and wound up in the federal prison in danbury 
conn for auto theft 
there he met the radical priests daniel and philip berrigan and 
joined their antiwar group out of prison in 1972 he moved to 
washington the following year launching his career as an activist 
with the community for creative nonviolence but cutting off all 
contact with his family 
snyder who was himself abandoned by his father when he was 9 
was apparently haunted the rest of his life by the family he failed 
to support 
his exwife ellen daly who remarried only got in touch with 
snyder again by telephone after he became famous 
i said to him on the phone mitchell forgive yourself i 
forgave you a long time ago she recalled in an interview in 
the washington post he said no thats his punishment to 
himself he said till the day i die ill never forgive myself 
 
he later visited his exwife and his sons ricky and dean both 
visited snyder at the shelter on one occasion helping serve 
thanksgiving dinner to the homeless 
snyders longtime companion carol fennelly told the post he 
would wake up at night having dreams about his deserted kids 
it would just prey on him 
two months ago fennelly was quoted as saying that she and 
snyder were planning to be married in september in a ceremony to 
be held in front of the communitys 1400bed shelter 
snyder and the community for creative nonviolence jumped to 
national prominence with his 1984 hunger strike that forced 
president reagan at the peak of his reelection campaign to 
promise a rundown federal building for a homeless shelter in 
downtown washington along with funds for renovation 
the episode was the focus of the madefortv movie samaritan 
the mitch snyder story starring martin sheen who referred to 
snyder as a saint the film scarcely mentioned snyders 
previous life in new york 
snyder drew increasingly harsh criticism in recent years for his 
abrasive style especially when he opposed the census bureaus 
effort this spring to count homeless people for the first time 
he refused to let census enumerators into his capitol hill 
shelter saying these people should be allowed to have their 
dignity and not be disturbed in the middle of the night to 
accommodate government grandstanding 
snyder recognized that he would win no popularity contests 
even among his friends 
i dont consider myself a good person he told the post i 
tend to be impatient i tend to be very short i tend to make heavy 
demands on people i dont have time or energy to give much 
oneonone and so im very hard on people around me i take much 
more than i give 
in march snyder announced that he was taking some time off to 
live in a trappist monastery in virginia 
im a religious person and from time to time its important 
to renew our relationship with god snyder told colleagues he 
said he wanted to take time for reflection to do simple work 
like baking bread 
after president bushs election in 1988 snyder proclaimed 
himself optimistic about the years to come 
i honestly believe george bush is a nicer person i believe 
ronald reagan was nice personally but his politics were 
meanspirited snyder said in a 1989 interview with the 
associated press 
listen to the music of tracy chapman of u2 they are 
harbingers of a shift in mood theres a 30year cycle the 30s 
the 60s the 90s weve just come through the me decade i 
think people have gotten sick of living only for themselves 
</TEXT>
