apparently designed to give the republic full control over kosovos 
media 
several leading ethnic albanian officials and journalists were 
removed from their jobs at kosovos radio television and the 
albanianlanguage rilindia publishing house which publishes a 
daily newspaper 
witnesses said serbias police entered downtown television 
radio and rilindia premises in the provincial capital of pristina 
arresting an unspecified number of ethnic albanian employees 
the state tanjug news agency reported that tv and radio later 
went off the air 
the serbian moves could trigger fresh unrest by the ethnic 
albanian majority in kosovo the nations least developed region 
and the scene of sporadic violence over the past two years 
the decision to disolve kosovos legislature and government was 
approved unanimously by all three chambers of serbias parliament 
it came in the wake of a declaration monday by 114 ethnic albanian 
deputies in kosovos provincial assembly to secede from serbia 
belgrade television said 
in the document kosovo proclaimed the province of 19 million 
equal to yugoslavias six republics and stated that ethnic 
albanians the thirdlargest ethnic group in the country would no 
longer be considered a national minority 
yugoslavia is a loose federation of six republics and two 
nominally autonomous provinces kosovo which is 90 percent ethnic 
albanian has progressively lost control of its affairs to serbia 
kosovos assembly has for a long time acted against the 
interests of the people of serbia belgrade radio quoted a 
serbian parliamentary statement that explained the new legislation 
as saying 
the decision to disband kosovos 188member legislature and 
local government headed by premier jusuf zeinulahu was read 
during thursdays assembly session said sources in the provincial 
capital of pristina 
