proposal was intended to demonstrate that nato is changing its 
focus to keep pace with events in the east three warsaw pact 
countries hungary czechoslovakia and poland have abandoned the 
communist system gorbachev meanwhile is in the midst of a 
struggle in the 28th communist party congress in moscow to gain 
endorsement of his experimentation with freemarket concepts 
if nato adopts the change in strategic doctrine proposed by bush 
there still would be us nuclear weapons in western europe but 
cuts in soviet troops in eastern and central europe and a 
reluctance by the warsaw pact allies to support a soviet invasion 
make their use highly unlikely us officials said 
bush also is ready to consider scrapping the 1470 us 
nucleartipped artillery shells now based mostly in west germany 
and reducing or eliminating an arsenal of 1560 nuclear bombs 
deployed in seven nato countries 
