<TEXT>
indonesia plans to spend 18 months 
celebrating its rich and diverse culture in the united states to 
promote trade tourism and investment 
the main aim of the festival is to acquaint the general 
american public with indonesia in all its aspects but especially 
its culture said mochtar kusumaatmadja who initiated the 
project he is a former cabinet minister in charge of foreign 
affairs and a graduate of yale university law school 
some people call it a coming out party he said 
although the worlds fifth most populous nation with more than 
175 million people 13677 islands 450 languages and the largest 
islamic community on earth indonesia sometimes seems invisible 
officials tell of americans who confuse it with india or indochina 
on the other hand many indonesians shun publicity some would 
be pleased if the world would just leave them alone 
geography has something to do with this no external enemy 
threatens and there is a true remoteness to be felt in parts of 
borneo the islands beyond bali and highland sumatra 
language and culture also play a part much of indonesias 
literary tradition is oral and rooted in specific islands it 
doesnt travel well or translate easily 
the yayasan nusantara jaya great archipelago foundation which 
mochtar heads planned the massive promotion because there is less 
awareness of the country among americans than in asia or europe 
also the united states is indonesias second largest trading 
partner after japan and a potential source of tourists 
americans have run out of countries to discover indonesia is 
one of the countries they see as a last frontier mochtar said 
jakarta has scheduled visit indonesia year 1991 as a major 
tourism campaign 
his foundation is private and the more than 6 million it 
raised for the festival came from donors such as major oil 
companies and the rockefeller foundation and ford foundation 
officials said the last time jakarta tried to penetrate the 
american market through a prolonged effort was with an elegant 
pavillion at the 1964 new york worlds fair 
another catalyst for the festival was the successful 18month 
celebration of india which drew much attention in 1985 ted tannen 
who designed the indian show is doing the same for indonesia 
five years in preparation the festival of indonesia 199091 
comprises exhibitions live performances movies and tv programs in 
13 cities the official opening is scheduled sept 16 at the 
kennedy center for performing arts in washington 
preliminaries include a showing of classical sculpture from the 
8th through the 15th century which opened july 1 at washingtons 
national gallery of art pieces from indonesias museums and 
archaeological services are supplemented by items loaned by 
european and us collections 
this will fall during the summer when there are thousands of 
people visiting the city so we dont want to miss the chance to 
promote the upcoming festival said operations manager rahmad 
adenan 
indonesias artistic styles range from the primitive carvings of 
new guinea and other islands to the finely crafted gold work of 
sumatra and java much of the folk art has never been seen in the 
west except in a few museums 
four exhibits are the core of the festival acting as 
centerpieces to scores of ancillary events they are the 
sculpture of indonesia the court arts of indonesia beyond 
the java sea and modern indonesian art three generations of 
tradition and change 19451990 
affiliated programs include exhibitions of traditional puppetry 
classical manuscripts and textiles 
museums presenting the core exhibitions include the national 
gallery and the smithsonian institution in washington new yorks 
metropolitan museum of art houstons museum of fine arts the 
dallas museum of art los angeles natural history museum and san 
franciscos asian arts museum 
</TEXT>
