its not grades and social 
events that preoccupy science students at ho chi minh university 
but crumbling buildings primitive equipment tattered books and 
crowded dorms 
in a decrepit building that wasnt new in french colonial days a 
half century ago a stairway reeked with the stench of a toilet 
in the physics lab students used equipment that belonged in a 
museum the newest book in the dusty chemistry library was 
published in 1974 
students said those who had to live on campus were packed seven 
or eight to rooms about 14 feet square that had one table a single 
light bulb and only intermittent electricity 
medical students said they didnt get enough to eat thats 
why we are so skinny said tran thanh cuong 27 
for the past two years vietnamese students have been 
increasingly vocal in demanding better conditions and even got the 
marxist curriculum revised 
sources said the authorities have yielded in hopes of avoiding 
the kind of student protests that challenged the chinese regime 
last year helped bring down communist governments in eastern 
europe and cause street battles with police in south korea 
