<TEXT>
world bank president barber conable on 
thursday urged the united states and other creditor nations to 
reduce debts owed them by poland and other middle income 
countries 
the bank the worlds biggest source of aid to developing 
nations considers the middle income countries as ranging from 
bolivia where the average citizen earns about 570 a year to a 
country like greece where the average annual income is 4800 
polands per capita income is about 2750 a year 
polands debt situation must be dealt with in some way 
conable said noting that poland is nearly 45 billion in debt 
clearly the debt service would make it very difficult for 
poland to resume growth and to make the necessary investments for 
getting a functioning economy with moving parts he said 
debt service refers to payments of interest and principal 
most polish debt is owed to governments with west germany and 
france the biggest creditors about 3 billion is owed to the us 
governments exportimport bank and commodity credit corp 
the world bank has lent poland 780 million in the past 12 
months conable said that was done on the assumption that some 
international settlement would be made on the remainder of polands 
official debt 
he said the debt burden makes it difficult for such countries to 
lure the investment they need to raise standards of living their 
own earnings go to keep up with the debt and foreign investors are 
wary as long as the burden exists 
he noted that president bush last week suggested that help with 
official debt be given in latin america 
clearly there are middle income countries elsewhere and other 
creditors besides the united states which must addresses this 
issue he said 
we hope it will be discussed at houston and it will be 
constructive if something could be worked out 
bush and leaders of six other major industrial countries hold 
their annual economic summit in houston beginning monday 
conable mentioned eastern european countries north africa 
nigeria and the ivory coast as candidates for help he pointed out 
that there already has been considerable reduction of official debt 
for the poorest countries especially in africa and that a plan 
pressed by treasury secretary nicholas f brady deals with debts to 
commercial banks 
the world bank estimates that of 1039 trillion worth of 
longterm debt owed by third world countries 517 billion comes 
from official sources that includes tens of billions owed to the 
world bank itself which conable did not discuss 
he suggested that government creditors might offer help of the 
same kind they have given the poorest countries these toronto 
terms named after the city where creditor governments agreed on 
them include reduction in total debt reduction of interest 
payments and a long stretchouts of repayments 
</TEXT>
