<TEXT>
mazda motor co will begin selling cars in east 
germany this fall opening about 50 dealerships in east berlin 
company officials said friday 
following similar moves by japans other large auto 
manufacturers mazda said it plans to sell between several hundred 
and 1000 cars this year 
officials said that already more than 500 east germans have 
applied for dealership contracts 
nissan motor co announced late last month that it intended to 
open between 60 and 70 dealer outlets in east germany by the end of 
1990 
toyota motor co japans largest car manufacturer and 
mitsubishi motor co have also indicated that they plan to begin 
marketing their vehicles in east germany 
though car sales in east germany totaled a modest 195000 
vehicles in 1989 potential demand is very strong as east germany 
moves toward economic and political unification with west germany 
company officials said japanese automakers estimate 1990 sales in 
the east at around 350000 vehicles 
